---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import img from '~/assets/shaggy.svg';
import { SiteDescription, SiteTitle } from '~/config';
import MarkdownLayout from '~/layouts/MarkdownLayout.astro';
---

<MarkdownLayout
	title={SiteTitle}
	description={SiteDescription}
	hide={['title', 'comments']}
	currentNav="Home"
>
	<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 xl:flex-row">
		<Picture class="lg:max-w-md" src={img} formats={['avif', 'webp']} alt="a dog" loading="eager" />
		<div>
			<h1>Hello there! I am Henalecam</h1>
			<p>
				This is a blog to describe my journey in the world of programming and technology. I am a
				software developer and I am passionate about learning new things. This blog is a way to
				share my knowledge and experiences with the world. I hope you find something useful here.
			</p>
			<ul class="list-disc">
				<li>
					Fast and light weight. Lighthouse 4 * 100/100 on desktop. 1 point decreased on mobile.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://astro.build">Astro 4</a> with no other UI frameworks integrated for better
					performance
				</li>
				<li>
					mobile-friendly responsive design with <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/">Tailwind CSS</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					Light / dark theme derived from <a href="https://github.com/varkai/hugo-theme-zozo"
						>hugo-theme-zozo</a
					>
				</li>
				<li>Markdown post support with emoji shortcode, katex</li>
				<li>static search with <a href="https://pagefind.app">Pagefind</a></li>
				<li>comment system powered by <a href="https://github.com/giscus/giscus">giscus</a></li>
				<li>SEO-friendly setup with canonical URLs and OpenGraph data</li>
				<li>RSS / Sitemap.xml / dynamic open graph image generation</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</MarkdownLayout>
